<div class="c290_4"> 
<div id="v290.4.1"><span class="H3117 s">And in that day</span><span class="H7651 s"> seven</span><span class="H802 s"> women</span><span class="H2388 s"> shall take hold</span><span class="H259 s"> of one</span><span class="H376 s"> man</span><span class="H559 s">, saying</span><span class="H398 s">, We will eat</span><span class="H3899 s"> our own bread</span><span class="H3847 s">, and wear</span><span class="H8071 s"> our own apparel</span><span class="H7121 s">: only let us be called</span><span class="H8034 s"> by thy name</span><span class="H622 s">, to take away</span><span class="H2781 s"> our reproach</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (let…: Heb. let thy name be called upon us) (to take…: or, take thou away)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.4.2"><span class="H3117 s">In that day</span><span class="H6780 s"> shall the branch</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H6643 s"> be beautiful</span><span class="H3519 s"> and glorious</span><span class="H6529 s">, and the fruit</span><span class="H776 s"> of the earth</span><span class="H1347 s"> <i>shall be</i> excellent</span><span class="H8597 s"> and comely for</span><span class="H6413 s"> them that are escaped</span><span class="H3478 s"> of Israel</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (beautiful…: Heb. beauty and glory) (them…: Heb. the escaping)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.4.3"><span class="H7604 s">And it shall come to pass, <i>that he that is</i> left</span><span class="H6726 s"> in Zion</span><span class="H3498 s">, and <i>he that</i> remaineth</span><span class="H3389 s"> in Jerusalem</span><span class="H559 s">, shall be called</span><span class="H6918 s"> holy</span><span class="H3789 s">, <i>even</i> every one that is written</span><span class="H2416 s"> among the living</span><span class="H3389 s"> in Jerusalem</span>: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (among…: or, to life)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.4.4"><span class="H136 s">When the Lord</span><span class="H7364 s"> shall have washed away</span><span class="H6675 s"> the filth</span><span class="H1323 s"> of the daughters</span><span class="H6726 s"> of Zion</span><span class="H1740 s">, and shall have purged</span><span class="H1818 s"> the blood</span><span class="H3389 s"> of Jerusalem</span><span class="H7130 s"> from the midst</span><span class="H7307 s"> thereof by the spirit</span><span class="H4941 s"> of judgment</span><span class="H7307 s">, and by the spirit</span><span class="H1197 s"> of burning</span>.</div> 
<div id="v290.4.5"><span class="H3068 s">And the LORD</span><span class="H1254 s"> will create</span><span class="H4349 s"> upon every dwelling place</span><span class="H2022 s"> of mount</span><span class="H6726 s"> Zion</span><span class="H4744 s">, and upon her assemblies</span><span class="H6051 s">, a cloud</span><span class="H6227 s"> and smoke</span><span class="H3119 s"> by day</span><span class="H5051 s">, and the shining</span><span class="H3852 s"> of a flaming</span><span class="H784 s"> fire</span><span class="H3915 s"> by night</span><span class="H3519 s">: for upon all the glory</span><span class="H2646 s"> <i>shall be</i> a defence</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (upon all: or, above all) (defence: Heb. covering)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.4.6"><span class="H5521 s">And there shall be a tabernacle</span><span class="H6738 s"> for a shadow</span><span class="H3119 s"> in the daytime</span><span class="H2721 s"> from the heat</span><span class="H4268 s">, and for a place of refuge</span><span class="H4563 s">, and for a covert</span><span class="H2230 s"> from storm</span><span class="H4306 s"> and from rain</span>.</div></div> 
